# Limit the Docker build context for website-agent/deploy/Dockerfile.
#
# The Fly builder uploads the entire context on every deploy, so we
# exclude everything that's not referenced by any Dockerfile in the
# repo. The vouch-agent image only needs:
#   - go-sidecar/  (excluding test fixtures)
#   - website-agent/backend/  (vouch_agent/, knowledge/, pyproject.toml)
#   - website-agent/deploy/   (Dockerfile, start.sh, did.json)
#
# Other Dockerfiles in the repo (examples/hasura/, vouch/bridge/,
# website-agent/backend/Dockerfile) reference paths inside their own
# subtree, so these excludes do not break them. Add narrower
# .dockerignore files alongside those Dockerfiles if you ever need to
# customise per-image.

# --- VCS, editor, OS noise -------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.github
.idea
.vscode
.claude
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# --- Build outputs & caches -----------------------------------------------
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/out
**/dist
**/build
**/.venv
**/venv
**/.cache

# --- Large dirs unrelated to the agent image ------------------------------
mobile
website
typescript
packages
browser-extension
c2pa-ca
cloudflare-worker
github-app-worker
examples
docs/blog
tests
papers
notes
vouch-protocol-pre-rewrite-backup
vouch-protocol-pro

# --- Secrets — defence in depth (these should never reach a builder) ------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/secrets
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/*.jwk
**/seed.hex
